  "text": "Suppose Alice does not know the true underlying probability distribution P , and she guesses according to some guessing function G. Sundaresan proved that the penalty in this mismatched guessing is again measured by the I α -divergence [CITATION_1] Th. 6] . This can be refined to the following theorem.",
